We aim to take reasonable steps to allow you to correct, amend, delete,
or limit the use of your Personal Data.
Please see section 15 (Contacting Us About Privacy Questions or Concerns) below.
In certain circumstances, you have the following data protection rights:
• The right to access, update or to delete the information we have on you.
• The right of rectification. You have the right to have your information rectified if that information is inaccurate or incomplete.
• The right to object. You have the right to object to our processing of your Personal Data.
• The right of restriction. You have the right to request us to restrict the processing of your personal information.
• The right to data portability. You have the right to be provided with a copy of the information we have on you.
• The right to withdraw consent. You also have the right to withdraw your consent at
  any time where we relied on your consent to process your personal information.
