10. COOKIE USAGE
While you access the Site, we may use the industry practice of placing a small amount of data that will be saved by your browser (“Cookies”).
This information can be placed on your computer or other devices used to visit the Site.
This information helps us recognize you as a customer,
collect information about your use of our Services/Products to better customize our services and better your experience.
We may also use the information collected to ensure compliance with our compliance program,
and to ensure your account security has not been compromised by detecting irregular or suspicious account activities.
Most browsers are setup to accept Cookies automatically.
Some Cookies expire when you finalize the session and other Cookies remain on your computer or other devices until deleted or expired.
You have the option to decline the use of our Cookies, but this may affect the functionality of the Services/Products or your user experience.
Some browsers have a do not track feature that lets you tell websites that you do not want to have your online activities tracked.
